content: I like the idea of structuring my commute time into focused blocks. I think I'll start by allocating 30 minutes for audiobook listening, 20 minutes for journaling or reflection, and 10 minutes for quick planning or organization. I'll also try to incorporate some language learning into my commute time, maybe 10 minutes a day. Do you think it's a good idea to prioritize my most important task for the day during my commute, or should I save it for when I get to the office?
